* EXP

** 9 to 8*

  - Export the 9 database with the 8 export tool and import it too
    with the 9 import tool.

** 9 to 7

  - Not supported.

** Pipe Import


  <example>
    #   Create a pipe.
    $ mknod exp.pipe p
    #   Needs the character single ampersand character.
    $ gunzip -c > exp.dmp.gz & \
      imp 'userid=ops$midba/midba' file=exp.pipe \
      'fromuser=ops$midba' 'touser=ops$midba'
  </example>

** Pipe Export

  <example>
    $ mknod exp.pipe p
    $ gzip dumpfile.dmp < exp.pipe &
    $ exp uid/pwd file=exp.pipe ...
  </example>

** Compress

  - Places all data into one extent.

* EXPDP

  - exp of the midba-Schema did no longer work with 10.2.0.3 so we
    switched to the data pump utility.

** Default Direcotry On Server Side

  - $ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/log
  - see too the two files dba-expdp.sh and dba-impdp.sh

** Drop Failed Export Job

SQL> select job_name from dba_datapump_jobs;
SQL> drop table <job_name>;
